Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology (JKUAT) [Elvis Ogina, Standard]  A mechanical engineering university student charged with wearing a police uniform is expected in court on October 19 for his bond terms.  Lambert Adrian Bartebess of the Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology denied the charge before Chief Magistrate Francis Andayi. He was also required to present a university identification card.  He is said to have committed the offense on Tuesday on Harry Thuku Road in Nairobi.  In the same court, a tout was charged with two counts of damaging a police vehicle and resisting arrest. Jackson Onsongo, who operates on Rongai route, denied the charges.   Top 2020 KCSE candidates to study medicine at UoN  Kenya's most attractive universities revealed  Top 2020 KCSE candidates to study medicine at UoN  Kenya's most attractive universities revealed  Wanafunzi wa chuo cha JKUAT wajipata matatani baada ya kujaribu kulaghai benki moja nchini |KTN MBIU  Wanafunzi wa JKUAT Kakamega wateta baada ya chuo chao kufungwa na kuagizwa kuhamia bewa la Kitale  Police recover a number stolen mobile phones in Nairobi By Hudson Gumbihi | 21 hours ago By Kamau Muthoni | 22 hours ago By Sirajurahman Abdullahi | 22 hours ago By Kamore Maina | 1 day ago